criteria.textblock:
        1.Inclusion criteria: Patients who meet the following criterion can be included in this
        study.

          1. Hypertension patients with positive PA screening (ARR>20) and at least one positive PA
             confirmatory test (PAC-post CCT>110pg/ml, PAC-post SSIT >80pg/ml, or PAC-post
             FST>60pg/ml);

          2. Willing to undergo AVS;

          3. Understand the whole process of the trial and voluntarily accept randomized grouping,
             intervention and follow-up;

          4. Voluntarily participate in the study and sign the informed consent form;

          5. Aged between 18-70, male or female, with legal capacity;

        2.Exclusion criteria: Patients with one of the following conditions will be excluded in
        this study:

          1. Pregnant or lactating women;

          2. Refusal to undergo unilateral adrenalectomy;

          3. Allergic to ACTH or contrast media;

          4. PA combined with Cushing syndrome (including subclinical Cushing): Cortisol was
             greater than 140nmol/ L after 1mg DST;

          5. Familial PA;

          6. Treatment with glucocorticoids and cannot be stopped;

          7. Complicated with disease which contraindicated to unilateral adrenalectomy or
             seriously interfere with subsequent treatment of PA or health-related quality of life
             assessment, such as severe heart disease (including pacemaker implantation), severe
             cardiac dysfunction, severe anemia (Hb<60g/L), stroke or acute coronary syndrome
             within 3 months, severe ascites and liver cirrhosis, malignant tumors;

          8. Alcoholics, drug users, and mentally disabled patients;

          9. CT does not exclude pheochromocytoma or cortical carcinoma.
